The second set of CSS rules target the `:hover` state of the `.my-hover-element` class. When a user hovers their mouse over an element with this class, its background color will change, and it will be scaled up to 150% of its original size. This creates an attention-grabbing animation that could be used, for example, to make buttons more interesting or to draw attention to important elements on a webpage.

